I need to identify the line item that represents the profit retained after all expenses have been deducted.

Looking at the cash flow statement, I can see that "Net Profit" represents the amount of profit after all expenses have been accounted for. This is typically the bottom line figure that shows what the company earned after deducting all operating costs, interest, taxes, etc.

From the table, I can see that Net Profit is listed as 143922.03 on 2024-02-04.

Therefore, the value of the retained profit is 143922.03.
